        <span class="s1">self.reset()</span>

    <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">reset(self):</span>
        <span class="s1">self._total_rel = </span><span class="s2">0  </span><span class="s0"># total sequence received</span>
        <span class="s0"># category counters, each integer counts sequence in its category</span>
        <span class="s1">self._rel_sample = [</span><span class="s2">0</span><span class="s1">] * self.NUM_OF_CATEGORY</span>
        <span class="s0"># if last byte in current buffer is not the last byte of a character,</span>
        <span class="s0"># we need to know how many bytes to skip in next buffer</span>
        <span class="s1">self._need_to_skip_char_num = </span><span class="s2">0</span>
        <span class="s1">self._last_char_order = -</span><span class="s2">1  </span><span class="s0"># The order of previous char</span>
        <span class="s0"># If this flag is set to True, detection is done and conclusion has</span>
        <span class="s0"># been made</span>
        <span class="s1">self._done = </span><span class="s3">False</span>

    <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">feed(self</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">byte_str</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">num_bytes):</span>
        <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">self._done:</span>
            <span class="s3">return</span>

        <span class="s0"># The buffer we got is byte oriented, and a character may span in more than one</span>
        <span class="s0"># buffers. In case the last one or two byte in last buffer is not</span>
        <span class="s0"># complete, we record how many byte needed to complete that character</span>
        <span class="s0"># and skip these bytes here.  We can choose to record those bytes as</span>
        <span class="s0"># well and analyse the character once it is complete, but since a</span>
        <span class="s0"># character will not make much difference, by simply skipping</span>
        <span class="s0"># this character will simply our logic and improve performance.</span>
        <span class="s1">i = self._need_to_skip_char_num</span>
        <span class="s3">while </span><span class="s1">i &lt; num_bytes:</span>
            <span class="s1">order</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">char_len = self.get_order(byte_str[i : i + </span><span class="s2">2</span><span class="s1">])</span>
            <span class="s1">i += char_len</span>
            <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">i &gt; num_bytes:</span>
                <span class="s1">self._need_to_skip_char_num = i - num_bytes</span>
                <span class="s1">self._last_char_order = -</span><span class="s2">1</span>
            <span class="s3">else</span><span class="s1">:</span>
                <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">(order != -</span><span class="s2">1</span><span class="s1">) </span><span class="s3">and </span><span class="s1">(self._last_char_order != -</span><span class="s2">1</span><span class="s1">):</span>
                    <span class="s1">self._total_rel += </span><span class="s2">1</span>
                    <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">self._total_rel &gt; self.MAX_REL_THRESHOLD:</span>
                        <span class="s1">self._done = </span><span class="s3">True</span>
                        <span class="s3">break</span>
                    <span class="s1">self._rel_sample[</span>
                        <span class="s1">jp2_char_context[self._last_char_order][order]</span>
                    <span class="s1">] += </span><span class="s2">1</span>
                <span class="s1">self._last_char_order = order</span>

    <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">got_enough_data(self):</span>
        <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s1">self._total_rel &gt; self.ENOUGH_REL_THRESHOLD</span>

    <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">get_confidence(self):</span>
        <span class="s0"># This is just one way to calculate confidence. It works well for me.</span>
        <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">self._total_rel &gt; self.MINIMUM_DATA_THRESHOLD:</span>
            <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s1">(self._total_rel - self._rel_sample[</span><span class="s2">0</span><span class="s1">]) / self._total_rel</span>
        <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s1">self.DONT_KNOW</span>

    <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">get_order(self</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">_):</span>
        <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s1">-</span><span class="s2">1</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s2">1</span>


<span class="s3">class </span><span class="s1">SJISContextAnalysis(JapaneseContextAnalysis):</span>
    <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">__init__(self):</span>
        <span class="s1">super().__init__()</span>
        <span class="s1">self._charset_name = </span><span class="s4">&quot;SHIFT_JIS&quot;</span>

    <span class="s1">@property</span>
    <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">charset_name(self):</span>
        <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s1">self._charset_name</span>

    <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">get_order(self</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">byte_str):</span>
        <span class="s3">if not </span><span class="s1">byte_str:</span>
            <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s1">-</span><span class="s2">1</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s2">1</span>
        <span class="s0"># find out current char's byte length</span>
        <span class="s1">first_char = byte_str[</span><span class="s2">0</span><span class="s1">]</span>
        <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">(</span><span class="s2">0x81 </span><span class="s1">&lt;= first_char &lt;= </span><span class="s2">0x9F</span><span class="s1">) </span><span class="s3">or </span><span class="s1">(</span><span class="s2">0xE0 </span><span class="s1">&lt;= first_char &lt;= </span><span class="s2">0xFC</span><span class="s1">):</span>
            <span class="s1">char_len = </span><span class="s2">2</span>
            <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">(first_char == </span><span class="s2">0x87</span><span class="s1">) </span><span class="s3">or </span><span class="s1">(</span><span class="s2">0xFA </span><span class="s1">&lt;= first_char &lt;= </span><span class="s2">0xFC</span><span class="s1">):</span>
                <span class="s1">self._charset_name = </span><span class="s4">&quot;CP932&quot;</span>
        <span class="s3">else</span><span class="s1">:</span>
            <span class="s1">char_len = </span><span class="s2">1</span>

        <span class="s0"># return its order if it is hiragana</span>
        <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">len(byte_str) &gt; </span><span class="s2">1</span><span class="s1">:</span>
            <span class="s1">second_char = byte_str[</span><span class="s2">1</span><span class="s1">]</span>
            <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">(first_char == </span><span class="s2">202</span><span class="s1">) </span><span class="s3">and </span><span class="s1">(</span><span class="s2">0x9F </span><span class="s1">&lt;= second_char &lt;= </span><span class="s2">0xF1</span><span class="s1">):</span>
                <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s1">second_char - </span><span class="s2">0x9F</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">char_len</span>

        <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s1">-</span><span class="s2">1</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">char_len</span>

        <span class="s3">if not </span><span class="s1">byte_str:</span>

        <span class="s3">else</span><span class="s1">:</span>

        <span class="s0"># return its order if it is hiragana</span>
        <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">len(byte_str) &gt; </span><span class="s2">1</span><span class="s1">:</span>

        <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s1">-</span><span class="s2">1</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">char_len</span>
